  <header>
    <title>Roadmap</title>
  </header>
  <body>
    <section id="status">
      <title>Overview</title>
      <p>
        At the moment we still only release alpha versions of Schoorbs since many features are 
        rewritten or evaluated if they are secure. With this site we want to present you what our
        main goals are in the next coming alpha versions. 
      </p>
    </section>
    <section id="schoorbs-1.0-alpha-1">
      <title>Schoorbs 1.0-Alpha 1</title>
      <p>
        <strong>Released:</strong> 
        <a href="http://xhochy.org/en/2007/07/05/schoorbs-10-alpha-1-released/">Alpha 1 Announcement 
        on the english XhochY Weblog.</a> 
      </p>
    </section>
    <section id="schoorbs-1.0-alpha-2">
      <title>Schoorbs 1.0-Alpha 2</title>
      <p>
        <strong>Released:</strong> 
        <a href="http://xhochy.org/en/2007/11/03/schoorbs-10-alpha-2-released/">Alpha 2 Announcement 
        on the english XhochY Weblog.</a> 
      </p>
    </section>
    <section id="schoorbs-1.0-alpha-3">
      <title>Schoorbs 1.0-Alpha 3</title>
      <ul>
        <li>Fixed AUTH/DB</li>
        <li>Fixed DB/MySQLi</li>
        <li>more and better Unit Tests -> BuildBot</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section id="schoorbs-1.0-alpha-4">
      <title>Schoorbs 1.0-Alpha 4</title>
      <ul>
        <li>Javascript- and CSS-files should now be deployed compressed</li>
        <li>Add a backup function to the Web-Admin-GUI</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section id="schoorbs-1.0-alpha-5">
      <title>Schoorbs 1.0-Alpha 5</title>
      <ul>
        <li>Rewritten search interface, results will be flavoured with hCalendar-mircoformat</li>
        <li>E-Mail support should become stable</li>
        <li>Languagefiles should be stored as .po's and imported into Launchpad</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section id="schoorbs-1.0-alpha-6">
      <title>Schoorbs 1.0-Alpha 6</title>
      <ul>
        <li>Ubuntu/Debian-package</li>
        <li>Installationscript</li>
        <li>Rewritten report function with PDF export</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
    <section id="schoorbs-1.0-alpha-7">
      <title>Schoorbs 1.0-Alpha 7</title>
      <ul>
        <li>Support for PHP accelerators/cachers (especially APC)</li>
        <li>Export a week as iCal</li>
        <li>...</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
